edia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic women's andmen's triathlonsto\", \"from\": 341, \"to\": 382}, {\"ngram\": \"Wednesday\", \"from\": 395, \"to\": 404}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 406, \"to\": 410}, {\"ngram\": \"lower levels\", \"from\": 463, \"to\": 475}, {\"ngram\": \"bacteria\", \"from\": 479, \"to\": 487}, {\"ngram\": \"days\", \"from\": 496, \"to\": 500}, {\"ngram\": \"uncertainty\", \"from\": 504, \"to\": 515}, {\"ngram\": \"heavy rains\", \"from\": 569, \"to\": 580}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's triathlon had been scheduled to take place on Tuesday, July 30, but was postponed until Wednesday after the river failed water quality tests.\", \"from\": 584, \"to\": 735, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The men's triathlon\", \"from\": 584, \"to\": 603}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 631, \"to\": 636}, {\"ngram\": \"Tuesday\", \"from\": 640, \"to\": 647}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 649, \"to\": 653}, {\"ngram\": \"Wednesday\", \"from\": 682, \"to\": 691}, {\"ngram\": \"the river\", \"from\": 698, \"to\": 707}]}, {\"sentence\": \"News that the races would go ahead on Wednesday came as a relief for teams and athletes, as well as for Paris authorities who have promised residents a swimmable Seine as a long-term legacy of the Games, with the triathlon a very public test.\", \"from\": 737, \"to\": 979, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 841, \"end\": 846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999974989, \"rank\": 2.6063757218806623e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 899, \"end\": 904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.999999998797648, \"rank\": 1.1663392490218048e-09, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sei